<StringTableFile>
  <Name>conversations\02_defiance_bay_first_fires\02_cv_ruins_vision</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>21</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You are from Creitum, my boy?" His words are an echo in your mind from a time long passed, and you know your response before you speak it, as if it has always been.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"You are from Creitum, my dear?" His words are an echo in your mind from a time long passed, and you know your response before you speak it, as if it has always been.</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes, I was born there."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Only recently."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I came to live there years ago."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What made you decide to join our order?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your teachings spoke to me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The world needs to know about the true gods."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The gods have been good to me and I wish to repay them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I went through dark times. Nothing made sense. That all changed when your order came to my homeland."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Remember never to be discouraged by those who cling to their beliefs. They are worthy of our pity, not our scorn."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The gods are just and they care for their faithful. I think that speaks to many people."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I saw the gods grant miracles to your order."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm honestly not sure."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"They will smile upon your service, as long as it is performed in earnest."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Little makes sense in the false contexts much of the world has lived under for so long. It is by the mercy of the gods that our faith has been able to reach so many of the heathen in more recent times."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So it is for all the faithful. To know the true gods is to be watched over by them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>The man chuckles. "As long as you are assured in your faith, the rest is not so important."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are you ready to take the oath? To spread the word of the gods to the lost and heathen?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I am..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A remarkable city. Truly one of the most impressive we have encountered outside of our own. Many exceptional people who have joined our cause come from Creitum."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>In front of you looms the ghostly, hollow image of the man who was present at your Awakening. He casts a pale, sickly light in the dank corridor as he regards you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>